<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,186,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis &amp; Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hardy" authorityName="Hardy" box="[832,1058,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[832,980,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
Hardy
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzgerald" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="1998" box="[1116,1340,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis box="[1116,1216,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. evansi</emphasis>
Fitzgerald
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished most easily by color differences: 
<taxonomicName box="[716,864,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[716,864,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with thorax entirely orange (sometimes with some brown markings on thoracic pleurae), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="1998" box="[578,677,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis box="[578,677,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. evansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with thorax entirely black, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[1033,1161,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis box="[1033,1161,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with scutum black anteriorly and orange posteriorly, scutellum orange, thoracic pleurae and postnotum black. The male terminalia of these three species are very similar; all have strongly reduced gonostyli, gonocoxites with ventral posteromedian margin deeply cleft, posteromedian margin of epandrium with only small cleft, and lateral lobe of gonocoxites present with medial (inner surface) sloping into the genital chamber. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="1998" box="[770,869,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis box="[770,869,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. evansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very broad, shallow, V-shaped epandrial cleft (cleft about ¼ depth of sclerite) with a small median lobe, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[876,1005,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis box="[876,1005,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only a narrow notch posteromedially. The terminalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[410,559,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[410,559,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[615,744,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis box="[615,744,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ most in the shape of the gonostylus; in posterior view, the gonostylus of 
<taxonomicName box="[355,504,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[355,504,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is triangular apically while there is a distinct thumb-like apical development in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[369,520,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Figs. 29 &amp; 31</figureCitation>
) and in posterolateral view the apex of the gonostylus of 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1295,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[1149,1295,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very short and slightly hooked whereas that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[563,692,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis box="[563,692,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer and more digitate (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1126,1286,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[205,1384,185,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[202,1385,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Male terminalia. 27–30, P. schusteri sp. n., holotype. 27. Posterior. 28. Posterolateral. 29. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 30. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral. 31–32, P. americana Hardy. 31. Close up of gonostylus, posterior. 32. Close up of gonostylus, posterolateral (area behind tip of gonostylus lightened in order to make apex of gonostylus more visible). Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm (Figs. 29–32 slightly enlarged, not to scale).Abbreviations: c, cerci; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; i, inner (medial) surface of lateral lobe of gonocoxite; llgc, lateral lobe of gonocoxite; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141101/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Figs. 30 &amp; 32</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[1307,1436,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schusteri">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">P. schusteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[315,435,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[315,435,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-species-group (see Discussion) and will key to couplet 28 using 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1164,1316,618,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref10022" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy’s 1945</bibRefCitation>
key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="36" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,655,681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet honors Dr. Jack Schuster (UVGC), collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[1172,1270,655,681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
as well as the type series of several other recently described Guatemalan 
<taxonomicName box="[807,891,691,717]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzgerald" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2019" box="[984,1437,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Amerikeroplatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimorphicus">
<emphasis box="[984,1316,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Amerikeroplatus dimorphicus</emphasis>
Fitzgerald
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[159,307,727,754]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Keroplatidae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzgerald" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2020" box="[369,657,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Ditomyiidae" genus="Ditomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis box="[369,536,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Ditomyia nana</emphasis>
Fitzgerald
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[671,818,727,754]" class="Insecta" family="Ditomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ditomyiidae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,979,762,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,979,762,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">
